From: Felipe <fel.c18@gmail.com>
Date: 2026-05-16
Subject: VersionScript.cmake: bump minimum CMake to 3.5 (cmake 4.0+ compat)

cmake 4.0.x removeu compatibility com VERSION < 3.5. VersionScript.cmake
roda standalone via `cmake -P` (subshell), então o flag CMAKE_POLICY_VERSION_MINIMUM
do package.mk principal não chega aqui. Bump direto no script.

--- a/cmake/VersionScript.cmake
+++ b/cmake/VersionScript.cmake
@@ -17,7 +17,7 @@

 # 3. This notice may not be removed or altered from any source distribution.

-cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 2.8)
+cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.5)

 # CMake script that reads a VERSION file and the current git history and the calls configure_file().
 # This is used by version_file() in VersionString.cmake
